pageContext.claim: “I heard about New Zealand, how well it was doing. They just had a big surge. I heard about all these places. We are doing well. Florida is down now. California is down. Arizona's way down.”
pageContext.analysis: Hardly a "big surge," more like a minor blip in a country widely hailed for its effective response to the coronavirus. In terms of total cases, New Zealand ranks 160th in the world. In terms of deaths, it ranks 161st. In terms of cases or deaths per million people, it ranks 174th.
